%\section*{Preface}
%Generalizations of the differential geometry of forms and vector
%fields to the cases of quantum planes and quantum Lie algebras in
%particular are given.
%In an abstract formulation that incorporates many existing examples of
%differential geometry on quantum spaces we combine an exterior
%derivative, inner derivations, Lie derivatives, forms and functions
%all into one big algebra. For quantum Lie algebras we give
%implicit commutation relations
%for a left-invariant basis of 1-forms.\nopagebreak
