manipulations into their algebraic counterparts.)
Taking this diagram as the definition of a braided (and graded) commutator
we can now express all Cartan relations in graphical form:\\
\paragraph{Lie derivatives.} Note that $\Lio{i}{j}(\dl) = \delta _{i}^{j} \dl$
because $\dl$ is invariant.\\
